string-array.item: vA is a 4-bit register with the value range v0 - v15\nvAA is an 8-bit register with a value range of v0 - v255\nvAAAA is a 16-bit register with a value range of v0 - v65535

0xF, 0xFF, etc. are used. to represent literal values. Like registers, the number F is used to represent a range of values, for example:\nThe range of 0xF values is represented by [-0x8, 0x7]\nThe range of values of 0xFF is represented by [-0x80, 0x7F]

V - void, Z - boolean, B - byte
C - char, S - short, I - int
J - long, F - float, D - double
void: can only be used for return types
boolean: stores the value true or false
byte: stores an integer from -128 to 127 and occupies 1 byte
short: stores an integer from -32768 to 32767 and takes 2 bytes
int: stores an integer from -2147483648 to 2147483647 and occupies 4 bytes
long: stores an integer from -9223372036854775808 to 9223372036854775807 and occupies 8 bytes
double: stores a floating point number from ±4.9*10³²⁴ to ±1.7976931348623157*10³⁰⁸ and occupies 8 bytes. A dot is used as the decimal separator in fractional literals.
float: stores a floating point number from -3.4*10³⁸ to 3.4*10³⁸ and occupies 4 bytes
char: stores a single character in UTF-16 encoding and occupies 2 bytes, so the range of stored values is from 0 to 65535.
Moves the value of register vB to register vA.
Moves the value of the vBBBB register to the vAA register.
Moves the value of the vBBBB register to the vAAAA register.
Moves the long/double value of register pair (vB, vB+1) to register pair vA, vA+1.
Moves the long/double value of a register pair (vBBBB, vBBBB+1) to a register pair vAA, vAA+1.
Moves the long/double value of a register pair (vBBBB, vBBBB+1) to a register pair vAAAA, vAAAA+1.
Moves an object reference from the vB register to the vA register.
Moves an object reference from the vBBBB register to the vAA register.
Moves an object reference from the vBBBB register to the vAAAA register.
Moves the return value of the previously called method into the vAA register.
Moves the long/double value returned by the previously called method into the register pair vAA, vAA+1.
Moves the object reference returned by the previously called method into the vAA register.
Moves the reference to the excluded object issued during the method call (during execution) to the vAA register.
Return by returning the value from the vAA register.
Return by returning a double/long value into a pair of registers vAA, vAA+1.
Return by returning the value of the object reference from the vAA register.
Places a 4-bit constant into the vA register.
Places a 16-bit constant into the vAA register.
Places an integer constant into the vAA register.
Places a 16-bit constant into the upper bits of the vAA register. Used to initialize float (floating point) values.
Places a 16-bit integer constant into the register pair vAA, vAA+1, converting the integer constant to a long constant.
Places a 32-bit integer constant into the register pair vAA, vAA+1, converting the integer constant to a long constant.
Places a 64-bit constant into the register pair vAA, vAA+1.
Places a 16-bit constant into the top 16-bits of the register pair vAA, vAA+1. Used to initialize double (floating point) values.
Places a reference to the specified string in the vAA register.
Places a reference to the specified string in the vAA register.
Places a reference to the string constant (string) identified by string_id into the vAA register.
Gets the object monitor referenced by the vAA register.
Releases the object monitor referenced by the vAA register.
Checks whether an object reference contained in the vAA register can be cast to the class identified by type_id. Throws a ClassCastException if it cannot, otherwise continues execution.
Checks whether the contents of the vB register is an instance of the class identified by type_id. Sets register vA to non-zero if present, 0 if not.\nvA = vB instanceOf type ? 10
Determines the number of array elements from the vB register and places the value in the vA register.\nvA = vB.length
Creates an instance of an object type and places a reference to the created instance in the vAA register.
Creates a new array of type_id variables with the size of register vB elements and places a reference to the array in register vA.

Creates a new data array of type type_id and fills it with parameters (that is, no long/double arrays, but reference types are allowed). A reference to the newly created array can be obtained using the move-result-object statement immediately following this statement (if one is to be used).

Creates a new data array of type type_id and fills it with a range of parameters (that is, no long/double arrays, but reference types are acceptable). A reference to the newly created array can be obtained using the move-result-object statement immediately following this statement (if one is to be used).
Fills the array referenced in the vAA register with static data. The data location is the sum of the position of the present instruction and the offset.
Throws an exception object. A reference to the exception object in the vAA register.
Unconditionally jump to a short (integer) 8-bit offset.

Implements the Switch operator when the control constants are close to each other (in a row). The instruction uses an index table. The instruction offset for a particular case is determined by the vAA index. If the vAA index goes beyond the table, execution continues with the next statement (default).

Implements the Switch operator in case of a sparse table. The instruction uses a table that specifies offsets for each constant. If no matches are found in the table, then the next statement is executed (default case).
Compares the float (floating point) values in vBB and vCC and places the integer value in the vAA register:\nvAA = vBB < vCC ? yes: 1, no: -1, equal: 0
Compares the float (floating point) values in vBB and vCC and places the integer value in the vAA register:\nvAA = vBB < vCC ? yes: 1, no: -1, equal: 0
Compares the double (floating point) values in vBB and vCC and places the integer value in the vAA register:\nvAA = (vBB, vBB+1) < (vCC, vCC+1) ? y\nyes: 1, no: -1, equal: 0
Compares the double (floating point) values in vBB and vCC and places the integer value in the vAA register:\nvAA = (vBB, vBB+1) > (vCC, vCC+1) ? yes: 1, no: -1, equal: 0
Compares the long (integer) values in vBB and vCC and places the integer (integer) value in the vAA register:\nvAA = (vBB, vBB+1) > (vCC, vCC+1) ? yes: 1, no: -1, equal: 0
Jumps to the specified label if vA == vB. vA and vB contain integer values.\n(eq is short for Equals)
Jumps to the specified label if vA != vB. vA and vB contain integer values.\n(ne is short for Not Equals)
Jumps to the specified label if vA < vB. vA and vB contain integer values.\n(lt is short for Less Than)
Jumps to the specified label if vA <= vB. vA and vB contain integer values.\n(le is an abbreviation for Less than or Equal/Less or equal)
Jumps to the specified label if vA > vB. vA and vB contain integer values.\n(gt is short for Greater Than/More Than)
Jumps to the specified label if vA >= vB. vA and vB contain integer values.\n(ge is short for Greater than or Equal)
Jumps to the specified label if vAA == 0. vAA contains an integer value.\n(eqz is short for Equals to Zero)
Jumps to the specified label if vAA != 0. vAA contains an integer value.\n(nez is short for Not Equals to Zero)
Jumps to the specified label if vAA < 0. vAA contains an integer value.\n(ltz is short for Less Than Zero)
Jumps to the specified label if vAA <= 0. vAA contains an integer value.\n(lez is an abbreviation for Less than or Equal to Zero/Less or equal to zero)
Jumps to the specified label if vAA > 0. vAA contains an integer value.\n(gtz is short for Greater Than Zero)
Jumps to the specified label if vAA >= 0. vAA contains an integer value.\n(gez is an abbreviation for Greater than or Equal to Zero)
Gets an integer value at the index contained in vCC from the array referenced in vBB and places it in the vAA register.\nvAA = vBB[vCC]
Gets, at the index contained in vCC, from the array referenced in vBB, a double/long value and places it in the register pair vAA, vAA+1.\n(vAA, vAA+1) = vBB[vCC]
Receives, at the index contained in vCC, from the array referenced in vBB, a reference to the object and places it in the vAA register.\nvAA = vBB[vCC]
Gets, at the index contained in vCC, from the array referenced in vBB, a boolean value and places it in the vAA register.\nvAA = vBB[vCC]
Retrieves, at the index contained in vCC, from the array referenced in vBB, a byte (integer) value and places it in the vAA register.\nvAA = vBB[vCC]
Retrieves, at the index contained in vCC, from the array referenced in vBB, a char value and places it in the vAA register.\nvAA = vBB[vCC]
Retrieves, at the index contained in vCC, from the array referenced in vBB, a short (integer) value and places it in the vAA register.\nvAA = vBB[vCC]
Places the integer value from vAA into the array referenced in vBB with the element containing the vCC register.\nvBB[vCC] = vAA

Calls (runs) a virtual method with parameters. Parameters are indicated in curly braces. The first parameter (register v2) contains a reference to the class containing the called method, the second parameter (the contents of register v3) is passed to the called method.
Calls (runs) a virtual method with parameters directly from the parent class.
Calls (runs) a method with parameters without the permissions of the virtual method.

Calls (runs) a static method with parameters. Parameters are indicated in curly braces. The parameter (the contents of register v3) is passed to the called method. The class containing the called method is indicated after the curly braces.
Calls (runs) an interface method with parameters.
Calls (runs) a virtual method with parameters, but the parameters must be contained in registers with numbers in order.
Calls (runs) a virtual method with parameters directly from the parent class, but the parameters must be contained in registers with sequential numbers.
Calls (runs) a method with parameters without virtual method permissions, but the parameters must be contained in sequentially numbered registers.
Calls (runs) a static method with parameters, but the parameters must be contained in registers with sequential numbers.
Calls (runs) an interface method with parameters, but the parameters must be contained in sequentially numbered registers.
Calculates vA = -vB for values of type integer.
Calculates (vA, vA+1) = -(vB, vB+1) for values of type long (integer).
Calculates (vA, vA+1) = ~(vB, vB+1) for values of type long (integer).
Calculates (vA, vA+1) = -(vB, vB+1) for double (floating point) values.
Converts an integer from vB to a long and stores it in the register pair vA, vA+1.\n(vA, vA+1) = (long) vB
Converts an integer from vB to a float and stores it in the vA register.\nvA = (float) vB
Converts an integer from vB to a double (floating point) and stores it in a register pair vA, vA+1.\n(vA, vA+1) = (double) vB
Converts a long (integer) value from vB, vB+1 to an integer (integer) and stores it in the vA register.\nvA = (int) (vB, vB+1)
Converts a long (integer) value from vB, vB+1 to a float (floating point) and stores it in the vA register.\nvA = (float) (vB, vB+1)

Converts a float (floating point) value from vB to an integer (integer) value and stores it in the vA register.\nvA = (int)vB
Converts a float (floating point) value from vB to a long (integer) value and stores it in the register pair vA, vA+1.\n(vA, vA+1) = (long) vB
Converts a float (floating point) value from vB to a double (floating point) value and stores it in the register pair vA, vA+1.\n(vA, vA+1) = (double) vB

Calculates vBB + vCC and stores the result in the vAA register. All values are integer.\nvAA = vBB + vCC
Calculates vBB - vCC and stores the result in the vAA register. All values are integer.\nvAA = vBB - vCC
Calculates vBB * vCC and stores the result in the vAA register. All values are integer.\nvAA = vBB * vCC
Calculates vBB / vCC and stores the result in the vAA register. All values are integer.\nvAA = vBB / vCC
Calculates vBB % vCC and stores the result in the vAA register. All values are integer.\nvAA = vBB % vCC
Calculates vBB & vCC (logical AND) and stores the result in the vAA register. All values are integer.\nvAA = vBB & vCC
Calculates vBB | vCC (logical OR) and stores the result in the vAA register. All values are integer.\nvAA = vBB | vCC
Computes vBB ^ vCC (exclusive OR) and stores the result in the vAA register. All values are integer.\nvAA = vBB ^ vCC
Shifts vBB left by the number of bits specified by vCC and stores the result in the vAA register. All values are integer.\nvAA = vBB << vCC
Shifts vBB to the right by the number of bits specified by vCC and stores the result in the vAA register. All values are integer.\nvAA = vBB >> vCC
Shifts vBB without preserving sign to the right by the number of bits specified by vCC, and stores the result in the vAA register. All values are integer.\nvAA = vBB >>> vCC
Computes (vBB, vBB+1) + (vCC, vCC+1) and stores the result in the register pair vAA, vAA+1. All values are long (integer).\n(vAA, vAA+1) = (vBB, vBB+1) + (vCC, vCC+1)
Calculates (vBB, vBB+1) - (vCC, vCC+1) and stores the result in the register pair vAA, vAA+1. All values are long (integer).\n(vAA, vAA+1) = (vBB, vBB+1) - (vCC, vCC+1)
